section#bio
  .row
    .col-12.col-md-4.text-center.pb-3
      = image_tag "profile-photo.jpeg", class: 'w-75 rounded-circle'
    .col-12.col-md-8
      markdown:
        Bienvenidos!

        My name is Mario Ayala. I am currently a postdoctoral researcher at the Department of Mathematics at the Technical University of Munich (TU München).

        My research sits at the intersection of probability theory and mathematical physics. I am fascinated by the emergence of macroscopic laws from simple microscopic rules of interaction — the so-called micro-to-macro transition. Lately I have also been exploring connections between stochastic analysis and score-based generative models.

        My Erdős number is 4:

        Me ---> Frank Redig ---> Pablo A. Ferrari ---> Peter E. Ney ---> Paul Erdős

        Contact: mario.ayala.valenzuela "at" gmail.com

section#research.mt-4
  h2.mb-4 Research lines
  .row
    .col-12.col-md-4.mb-3
      .card.h-100.border-primary
        .card-body
          h5.card-title Fluctuation fields
          p.card-text Higher-order fluctuations for SEP, SIP, and IRW. Convergence via inductive triangular drift decompositions and L² vanishing estimates.
    .col-12.col-md-4.mb-3
      .card.h-100
        .card-body
          h5.card-title Applications of duality
          p.card-text Orthogonal duality polynomials (Krawtchouk, Meixner), empirical measure duality, and dressed fields absorbing the carré-du-champ anomaly.
    .col-12.col-md-4.mb-3
      .card.h-100
        .card-body
          h5.card-title Noise interpretation in SDEs
          p.card-text Itô, Stratonovich, and Klimontovich conventions. Reversibility under coarse-graining and stochastic integral choices in multiplicative noise.
